3309static void ParseTargetArgs(TargetOptions &Opts, ArgList &Args,
3310 DiagnosticsEngine &Diags) {
3311 Opts.CodeModel = getCodeModel(Args, Diags);
3312 Opts.ABI = Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_target_abi);
3313 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_meabi)) {
3314 StringRef Value = A->getValue();
3315 llvm::EABI EABIVersion = llvm::StringSwitch<llvm::EABI>(Value)
3316 .Case("default", llvm::EABI::Default)
3317 .Case("4", llvm::EABI::EABI4)
3318 .Case("5", llvm::EABI::EABI5)
3319 .Case("gnu", llvm::EABI::GNU)
3320 .Default(llvm::EABI::Unknown);
3321 if (EABIVersion == llvm::EABI::Unknown)
3322 Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << A->getAsString(Args)
3323 << Value;
3324 else
3325 Opts.EABIVersion = EABIVersion;
3326 }
3327 Opts.CPU = Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_target_cpu);
3328 Opts.FPMath = Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_mfpmath);
3329 Opts.FeaturesAsWritten = Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_target_feature);
3330 Opts.LinkerVersion = Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_target_linker_version);
3331 Opts.Triple = Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_triple);
3332 // Use the default target triple if unspecified.
3333 if (Opts.Triple.empty())
3334 Opts.Triple = llvm::sys::getDefaultTargetTriple();
3335 Opts.Triple = llvm::Triple::normalize(Opts.Triple);
3336 Opts.OpenCLExtensionsAsWritten = Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_cl_ext_EQ);
3337
3338 llvm::Triple T(Opts.Triple);
3339 if (T.isMIPS() && Opts.ABI == "sandbox") {
3340 // rename sandbox ABI to purecap ABI and output a deprecated warning
3341 Opts.ABI = "purecap";
3342 Diags.Report(diag::warn_cheri_sandbox_abi_is_purecap);
3343 }
3344 if (T.isMIPS()) {
3345 if (Opts.ABI != "purecap" && T.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::CheriPurecap) {
3346 // Can't use -mabi=64 with -purecap triple
3347 // Can't use -mabi=64 with -purecap triple
3348 if (Opts.ABI.empty())
3349 Opts.ABI = "purecap";
3350 else
3351 Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_abi_incompatible_with_triple) << Opts.ABI << T.str();
3352 } else if (Opts.ABI == "purecap") {
3353 if (T.getEnvironment() == llvm::Triple::UnknownEnvironment) {
3354 T.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::CheriPurecap);
3355 } else if (T.getEnvironment() != llvm::Triple::CheriPurecap) {
3356 // e.g. explicit gnuabin32 triple with -mabi=purecap
3357 Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_abi_incompatible_with_triple) << Opts.ABI << T.str();
3358 }
3359 }
3360 }
3361
3362 if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_cheri_size)) {
3363 // NOTE: Opts.Features is cleared after this so we need to add it to FeaturesAsWritten!
3364 Opts.FeaturesAsWritten.push_back("+chericap");
3365 StringRef CheriCPUName = llvm::StringSwitch<StringRef>(A->getValue())
3366 .Case("64", "+cheri64")
3367 .Case("128", "+cheri128")
3368 .Case("256", "+cheri256")
3369 .Default("");
3370 if (CheriCPUName.empty())
3371 Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
3372 Opts.FeaturesAsWritten.push_back(CheriCPUName);
3373 A->claim();
3374 }
3375 Opts.ForceEnableInt128 = Args.hasArg(OPT_fforce_enable_int128);
3376 Opts.NVPTXUseShortPointers = Args.hasFlag(
3377 options::OPT_fcuda_short_ptr, options::OPT_fno_cuda_short_ptr, false);
3378 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_target_sdk_version_EQ)) {
3379 llvm::VersionTuple Version;
3380 if (Version.tryParse(A->getValue()))
3381 Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
3382 << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
3383 else
3384 Opts.SDKVersion = Version;
3385 }
3386}
3387
3388bool CompilerInvocation::CreateFromArgs(CompilerInvocation &Res,
3389 const char *const *ArgBegin,
3390 const char *const *ArgEnd,
3391 DiagnosticsEngine &Diags) {
3392 bool Success = true;
3393
3394 // Parse the arguments.
3395 std::unique_ptr<OptTable> Opts = createDriverOptTable();
3396 const unsigned IncludedFlagsBitmask = options::CC1Option;
3397 unsigned MissingArgIndex, MissingArgCount;
3398 InputArgList Args =
3399 Opts->ParseArgs(llvm::makeArrayRef(ArgBegin, ArgEnd), MissingArgIndex,
3400 MissingArgCount, IncludedFlagsBitmask);
3401 LangOptions &LangOpts = *Res.getLangOpts();
3402
3403 // Check for missing argument error.
3404 if (MissingArgCount) {
3405 Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_missing_argument)
3406 << Args.getArgString(MissingArgIndex) << MissingArgCount;
3407 Success = false;
3408 }
3409
3410 // Issue errors on unknown arguments.
3411 for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_UNKNOWN)) {
3412 auto ArgString = A->getAsString(Args);
3413 std::string Nearest;
3414 if (Opts->findNearest(ArgString, Nearest, IncludedFlagsBitmask) > 1)
3415 Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_unknown_argument) << ArgString;
3416 else
3417 Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_unknown_argument_with_suggestion)
3418 << ArgString << Nearest;
3419 Success = false;
3420 }
3421
3422 Success &= ParseAnalyzerArgs(*Res.getAnalyzerOpts(), Args, Diags);
3423 Success &= ParseMigratorArgs(Res.getMigratorOpts(), Args);
3424 ParseDependencyOutputArgs(Res.getDependencyOutputOpts(), Args);
3425 Success &=
3426 ParseDiagnosticArgs(Res.getDiagnosticOpts(), Args, &Diags,
3427 false /*DefaultDiagColor*/, false /*DefaultShowOpt*/);
3428 ParseCommentArgs(LangOpts.CommentOpts, Args);
3429 ParseFileSystemArgs(Res.getFileSystemOpts(), Args);
3430 // FIXME: We shouldn't have to pass the DashX option around here
3431 InputKind DashX = ParseFrontendArgs(Res.getFrontendOpts(), Args, Diags,
3432 LangOpts.IsHeaderFile);
3433 ParseTargetArgs(Res.getTargetOpts(), Args, Diags);
3434 Success &= ParseCodeGenArgs(Res.getCodeGenOpts(), Args, DashX, Diags,
3435 Res.getTargetOpts(), Res.getFrontendOpts());
3436 ParseHeaderSearchArgs(Res.getHeaderSearchOpts(), Args,
3437 Res.getFileSystemOpts().WorkingDir);
3438 llvm::Triple T(Res.getTargetOpts().Triple);
3439 if (DashX.getFormat() == InputKind::Precompiled ||
3440 DashX.getLanguage() == InputKind::LLVM_IR) {
3441 // ObjCAAutoRefCount and Sanitize LangOpts are used to setup the
3442 // PassManager in BackendUtil.cpp. They need to be initializd no matter
3443 // what the input type is.
3444 if (Args.hasArg(OPT_fobjc_arc))
3445 LangOpts.ObjCAutoRefCount = 1;
3446 // PIClevel and PIELevel are needed during code generation and this should be
3447 // set regardless of the input type.
3448 LangOpts.PICLevel = getLastArgIntValue(Args, OPT_pic_level, 0, Diags);
3449 LangOpts.PIE = Args.hasArg(OPT_pic_is_pie);
3450 parseSanitizerKinds("-fsanitize=", Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_fsanitize_EQ),
3451 Diags, LangOpts.Sanitize);
3452 } else {
3453 // Other LangOpts are only initialized when the input is not AST or LLVM IR.
3454 // FIXME: Should we really be calling this for an InputKind::Asm input?
3455 ParseLangArgs(LangOpts, Args, DashX, Res.getTargetOpts(),
3456 Res.getPreprocessorOpts(), Diags);
3457 if (Res.getFrontendOpts().ProgramAction == frontend::RewriteObjC)
3458 LangOpts.ObjCExceptions = 1;
3459 if (T.isOSDarwin() && DashX.isPreprocessed()) {
3460 // Supress the darwin-specific 'stdlibcxx-not-found' diagnostic for
3461 // preprocessed input as we don't expect it to be used with -std=libc++
3462 // anyway.
3463 Res.getDiagnosticOpts().Warnings.push_back("no-stdlibcxx-not-found");
3464 }
3465 }
3466
3467 LangOpts.FunctionAlignment =
3468 getLastArgIntValue(Args, OPT_function_alignment, 0, Diags);
3469
3470 if (LangOpts.CUDA) {
3471 // During CUDA device-side compilation, the aux triple is the
3472 // triple used for host compilation.
3473 if (LangOpts.CUDAIsDevice)
3474 Res.getTargetOpts().HostTriple = Res.getFrontendOpts().AuxTriple;
3475 }
3476
3477 // Set the triple of the host for OpenMP device compile.
3478 if (LangOpts.OpenMPIsDevice)
3479 Res.getTargetOpts().HostTriple = Res.getFrontendOpts().AuxTriple;
3480
3481 // FIXME: Override value name discarding when asan or msan is used because the
3482 // backend passes depend on the name of the alloca in order to print out
3483 // names.
3484 Res.getCodeGenOpts().DiscardValueNames &=
3485 !LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::Address) &&
3486 !LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::KernelAddress) &&
3487 !LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::Memory) &&
3488 !LangOpts.Sanitize.has(SanitizerKind::KernelMemory);
3489
3490 ParsePreprocessorArgs(Res.getPreprocessorOpts(), Args, Diags,
3491 Res.getFrontendOpts().ProgramAction);
3492 ParsePreprocessorOutputArgs(Res.getPreprocessorOutputOpts(), Args,
3493 Res.getFrontendOpts().ProgramAction);
3494
3495 // Turn on -Wspir-compat for SPIR target.
3496 if (T.isSPIR())
3497 Res.getDiagnosticOpts().Warnings.push_back("spir-compat");
3498
3499 // If sanitizer is enabled, disable OPT_ffine_grained_bitfield_accesses.
3500 if (Res.getCodeGenOpts().FineGrainedBitfieldAccesses &&
3501 !Res.getLangOpts()->Sanitize.empty()) {
3502 Res.getCodeGenOpts().FineGrainedBitfieldAccesses = false;
3503 Diags.Report(diag::warn_drv_fine_grained_bitfield_accesses_ignored);
3504 }
3505 return Success;
3506}
3507
3508std::string CompilerInvocation::getModuleHash() const {
3509 // Note: For QoI reasons, the things we use as a hash here should all be
3510 // dumped via the -module-info flag.
3511 using llvm::hash_code;
3512 using llvm::hash_value;
3513 using llvm::hash_combine;
3514
3515 // Start the signature with the compiler version.
3516 // FIXME: We'd rather use something more cryptographically sound than
3517 // CityHash, but this will do for now.
3518 hash_code code = hash_value(getClangFullRepositoryVersion());
3519
3520 // Extend the signature with the language options
3521#define LANGOPT(Name, Bits, Default, Description) \
3522 code = hash_combine(code, LangOpts->Name);
3523#define ENUM_LANGOPT(Name, Type, Bits, Default, Description) \
3524 code = hash_combine(code, static_cast<unsigned>(LangOpts->get##Name()));
3525#define BENIGN_LANGOPT(Name, Bits, Default, Description)
3526#define BENIGN_ENUM_LANGOPT(Name, Type, Bits, Default, Description)
3527#include "clang/Basic/LangOptions.def"
3528
3529 for (StringRef Feature : LangOpts->ModuleFeatures)
3530 code = hash_combine(code, Feature);
3531
3532 // Extend the signature with the target options.
3533 code = hash_combine(code, TargetOpts->Triple, TargetOpts->CPU,
3534 TargetOpts->ABI);
3535 for (const auto &FeatureAsWritten : TargetOpts->FeaturesAsWritten)
3536 code = hash_combine(code, FeatureAsWritten);
3537
3538 // Extend the signature with preprocessor options.
3539 const PreprocessorOptions &ppOpts = getPreprocessorOpts();
3540 const HeaderSearchOptions &hsOpts = getHeaderSearchOpts();
3541 code = hash_combine(code, ppOpts.UsePredefines, ppOpts.DetailedRecord);
3542
3543 for (const auto &I : getPreprocessorOpts().Macros) {
3544 // If we're supposed to ignore this macro for the purposes of modules,
3545 // don't put it into the hash.
3546 if (!hsOpts.ModulesIgnoreMacros.empty()) {
3547 // Check whether we're ignoring this macro.
3548 StringRef MacroDef = I.first;
3549 if (hsOpts.ModulesIgnoreMacros.count(
3550 llvm::CachedHashString(MacroDef.split('=').first)))
3551 continue;
3552 }
3553
3554 code = hash_combine(code, I.first, I.second);
3555 }
3556
3557 // Extend the signature with the sysroot and other header search options.
3558 code = hash_combine(code, hsOpts.Sysroot,
3559 hsOpts.ModuleFormat,
3560 hsOpts.UseDebugInfo,
3561 hsOpts.UseBuiltinIncludes,
3562 hsOpts.UseStandardSystemIncludes,
3563 hsOpts.UseStandardCXXIncludes,
3564 hsOpts.UseLibcxx,
3565 hsOpts.ModulesValidateDiagnosticOptions);
3566 code = hash_combine(code, hsOpts.ResourceDir);
3567
3568 // Extend the signature with the user build path.
3569 code = hash_combine(code, hsOpts.ModuleUserBuildPath);
3570
3571 // Extend the signature with the module file extensions.
3572 const FrontendOptions &frontendOpts = getFrontendOpts();
3573 for (const auto &ext : frontendOpts.ModuleFileExtensions) {
3574 code = ext->hashExtension(code);
3575 }
3576
3577 // When compiling with -gmodules, also hash -fdebug-prefix-map as it
3578 // affects the debug info in the PCM.
3579 if (getCodeGenOpts().DebugTypeExtRefs)
3580 for (const auto &KeyValue : getCodeGenOpts().DebugPrefixMap)
3581 code = hash_combine(code, KeyValue.first, KeyValue.second);
3582
3583 // Extend the signature with the enabled sanitizers, if at least one is
3584 // enabled. Sanitizers which cannot affect AST generation aren't hashed.
3585 SanitizerSet SanHash = LangOpts->Sanitize;
3586 SanHash.clear(getPPTransparentSanitizers());
3587 if (!SanHash.empty())
3588 code = hash_combine(code, SanHash.Mask);
3589
3590 return llvm::APInt(64, code).toString(36, /*Signed=*/false);
3591}
3592
3593template<typename IntTy>
3594static IntTy getLastArgIntValueImpl(const ArgList &Args, OptSpecifier Id,
3595 IntTy Default,
3596 DiagnosticsEngine *Diags) {
3597 IntTy Res = Default;
3598 if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(Id)) {
3599 if (StringRef(A->getValue()).getAsInteger(10, Res)) {
3600 if (Diags)
3601 Diags->Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_int_value) << A->getAsString(Args)
3602 << A->getValue();
3603 }
3604 }
3605 return Res;
3606}

3628
3629IntrusiveRefCntPtr<llvm::vfs::FileSystem> createVFSFromCompilerInvocation(
3630 const CompilerInvocation &CI, DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
3631 IntrusiveRefCntPtr<llvm::vfs::FileSystem> BaseFS) {
3632 if (CI.getHeaderSearchOpts().VFSOverlayFiles.empty())
3633 return BaseFS;
3634
3635 IntrusiveRefCntPtr<llvm::vfs::FileSystem> Result = BaseFS;
3636 // earlier vfs files are on the bottom
3637 for (const auto &File : CI.getHeaderSearchOpts().VFSOverlayFiles) {
3638 llvm::ErrorOr<std::unique_ptr<llvm::MemoryBuffer>> Buffer =
3639 Result->getBufferForFile(File);
3640 if (!Buffer) {
3641 Diags.Report(diag::err_missing_vfs_overlay_file) << File;
3642 continue;
3643 }
3644
3645 IntrusiveRefCntPtr<llvm::vfs::FileSystem> FS = llvm::vfs::getVFSFromYAML(
3646 std::move(Buffer.get()), /*DiagHandler*/ nullptr, File,
3647 /*DiagContext*/ nullptr, Result);
3648 if (!FS) {
3649 Diags.Report(diag::err_invalid_vfs_overlay) << File;
3650 continue;
3651 }
3652
3653 Result = FS;
3654 }
3655 return Result;
3656}
